// Listing 6 from the paper: (min,+) convolution that benefits from optimizations on subadditive functions.
// Reference: Zippo & Stea, "An Efficient Parallel Network Calculus Library" (2023), doi:10.1109/TIT.2023.3244276
// Run with: nancy-playground run listing-6-subadditive-convolutions.mppg

f := star( ratency(5, 13) + 11 )
g := star( ratency(7, 17) + 15 )
h := star( ratency(11, 19) + 21 )
k := f * g * h
plot(f, g, h, k)
